# Commit Conventions

## Human Review Before Committing

**Never run `git commit` autonomously.** Always present staged files (`git diff --cached --stat`) and the proposed message for user approval first.

## Required Flags

Every `git commit` MUST use `-s` (DCO sign-off) and `-S` (GPG signature):

```bash
git commit -s -S -m "type(scope): description"
```

## Conventional Commits

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New feature, rule, or component reference |
| `fix` | Bug fix or correction |
| `docs` | Documentation-only changes |
| `chore` | Maintenance (gitignore, Makefile, submodule updates) |
| `refactor` | Restructuring without changing behavior |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `ci` | CI/CD configuration changes |

Scope is optional: `feat(rules): add security rule`.
